1	Stripper Wells	Despite their small output, stripper oil and gas wells make a significant  contribution to the nation's energy supply; they are the lifeblood of thousands of  small, independent oil and gas operating companies. About 80 percent of the  roughly 500,000 producing oil wells in the United States are classified as stripper  wells.	https://www.netl.doe.gov/research/oil-and-gas/stripper-wells
